<HEADLINE> Three Die in 140-Vehicle Expressway Pileup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and
at least six were injured in a traffic accident on the Langfang
Section of the Beijing-Tianjin Expressway today.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Traffic Control Department of Longfang City,
Hebei Province, said that the accident involved 140 motor vehicles
in a chain collision.
</P>
<P>
He said that the accident occurred at eight o'clock this
morning, and its direct cause was heavy fog. The accident caused a
traffic jam on a 12-kilometer long lane.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, traffic on the expressway was not halted, and
all the damaged cars had been removed from the expressway by
noon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
