<HEADLINE> Laos Hails Annan's Efforts in Solving Iraqi Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 26 (xinhua) -- The Laos government has welcomed
the settlement of the Iraqi weapons inspection crisis by UN
Secretary-General Kofi Annan, KPL news agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A Ministry of Foreign Affairs statement said that the Laos
People's Democratic Republic, as a peace-loving member of the
United Nations, had a strong desire to see conflicts settled
peacefully.
</P>
<P>
The Laos PDR fully supported the efforts of member countries of
the UN security council, as well as the international community,
in finding ways to settle the conflict without the use of force.
</P>
<P>
It also fully supported the successful efforts of Annan in
solving the conflict through diplomatic means, so as to avoid the
Iraqi people suffering, the statement said. enditem

