<HEADLINE> Canada Accepts 19 Cuban Political Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien announced Thursday that the Cuban government has agreed
to let 19 Cuban political prisoners come to Canada.
</P>
<P>
The 19 prisoners have agreed to come to Canada as a condition
of their release, Chretien said in a news release.
</P>
<P>
"The decision to release these prisoners demonstrate the
benefits of a policy of construction engagement with Cuba on a
broad range of issues, including sensitive political ones,"
Chretien said.
</P>
<P>
Immigration processing of the 19 individuals will begin
immediately, the government said. 
</P>
