<HEADLINE> Beijing Appoints 19 Government Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Jianmin, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Beijing Municipal People's Congress,
today presented letters of appointment to 19 government officials
in charge of departments of the Beijing Municipal Government.
</P>
<P>
The 19 officials were the first batch of department heads named
by Mayor Jia Qinglin since he and the deputy mayors were elected
at the first session of the 11th Beijing People's Congress in
January.
</P>
<P>
The First Session of the Standing Committee of the 11th Beijing
Municipal People's Congress, which concluded today, voted to
approve the appointment.
</P>
<P>
Of the 19 officials, three were newly elected -- Liu Zhihua
as secretary-general of the Beijing Municipal Government, Yuan Guiren
as director of the city's education commission, and Qin Gang
as director of the Beijing Municipal Supervision Department.
</P>
<P>
The other 16 officials renewed their terms of office, with
Zhang Liangji as head of the Beijing Municipal Public Security
Bureau and Qi Guosheng, 38, the youngest among them, as
director of the city's auditing department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
