<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, February 27 (Xinhua) -- An international seminar on
the late Chinese Premier Zhou Enlai opened in this north China
port city today to mark the centenary of the birth of the great
statesman.
</P>
<P>
Over 200 Chinese officials, as well as experts from Japan,
Russia, the United States, India and Britain are attending the
seminar. They will present 130 papers with the themes of
"Zhou Enlai and China", "Zhou Enlai and the World", and "Zhou Enlai
and International Cultural Exchanges".
</P>
