champion Maurice Greene and Jon Drummond at the Melbourne Grand
Prix meet.
</P>
<P>
Greene clocked the fastest time on Australian soil in running
10.06 seconds into a 1.6 meter per second headwind in Melbourne.
</P>
<P>
Greene said if there was no headwind he could have the chance
of breaking BAiley's world record of 9.84.
</P>
<P>
