<HEADLINE> Guangdong Province Curbs Inflation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 27 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province witnessed falling prices in January when compared with
the previous year's period.
</P>
<P>
Falling prices were recorded despite the fact that price hikes
normally accompany the period between New Year's and Spring
Festival.
</P>
<P>
The retail price index for the prosperous province dropped by
1.7 percent on a year-on-year basis, with the consumer goods index
falling by 0.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, the two indices rose by 0.2 percent and 0.5
percent respectively when compared to December levels.
</P>
<P>
January prices for aquatics products and fresh fruit climbed,
with falling prices for meat, poultry and eggs.
</P>
<P>
Prices for the major portion of 13 major daily necessities
dropped, and the index for farming materials fell by 6.5
percent. On the other hand, prices for service items jumped by 9.4
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
