<HEADLINE> Korda Missses Chance to Top Rankings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 26 (Xinhua) -- World number two Petr Korda
missed his chance to top the ATP world rankings on Thursday when
he lost in straight sets to Frenchman Cedric Pioline at the London
indoor tournament.
</P>
<P>
Korda, who needed to reach the semi-finals to surpass the
current world number one Peter Sampras, was beaten 6-3, 6-3 by
Pioline in his second round match which lasted only 77 minutes.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Open champion and world number three Pat Rafter of
Australia kept on course after scoring an easy 6-3, 7-6 win over
Sweden's Magnus Gustafsson. Rafter must now find a way past South
Africa's in-form Wayne Ferreira to reach the last four here.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Tim Henman beat Rainer Schuttler of Germany on
Thursday 4-6, 6-3, 6-4 to progress to a quarter-final clash with
Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
