<HEADLINE> Novotna Advance to Austrian Open Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Jana Novotna
eliminated French qualifier Amalie Mauresmo 6-4, 6-2 to enter the
quarter-finals of the Austrian Open WTA tournament at Linz on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Novotna, ranked third in the world, will now face Anna
Kournikova of Russia in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Fifth-seeded Lisa Raymond of the United States won the two
tie-breakers 7-6 (7-5), 7-6 (7-3) to beat Miriam Oremans of the
Netherlands. Raymond will take on second-seeded Iva Majoli of
Croatia in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
The other two quarter-final matches will be played between
seventh-seed Sabine Appelmans and Dominique Van Roost, Nathalie
Tauziat and Silvia Farina. 
</P>
