<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Economic Management Assistance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 26 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved on
Thursday a 15 million U.S. dollar loan for an economic management
project in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
This project will provide technical assistance to improve the
capacity of the Thai government for effective management of the
country's economy, which has been adversely affected by the recent
currency and banking crisis.
</P>
<P>
The project will finance measures to upgrade macroeconomic
management and public administration, reform public enterprises
and strengthen the competitiveness of Thailand's industrial
sector.
</P>
<P>
The project is also designed to help contribute to a revival of
economic growth and renewed export performance by bolstering the
effectiveness of the public sector as well as the competitiveness
of private industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
