<DOCNO> XIE19980227.0287 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Stocks End Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Despite profit-taking on
gains, major market indicators on the New York Stock Exchange
(NYSE) Thursday soared to new highs with the Dow Jones industrial
average moving 32.89 points up to close at 8,490.67, the highest
level in its history.
</P>
<P>
On the NYSE, advancing issues beat decliners 3-2 with 1,738 up,
1,130 down and 572 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
A total of 645.79 million shares changed hands against 608.36
million shares on Wednesday, preliminary figures show.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 5.75 to close at
1,048.65, and the technology-heavy Nastaq composite index rose
10.63 to 1,777.11. The two indexes finished at their record highs
for the third consecutive session this week.
</P>
<P>
On the small companies' front, the Russell 2000 index rose 3.08
to 461.57 and the American Stock Exchange composite index edged up
8.63 to 700.42.  
</P>
</TEXT>
